name: Paleo Teriyaki Stir-Fry Zoodles (Gluten Free)
author: Beth Smith
summary: This is a paleo-friendly, gluten-free Asian-inspired zoodle recipe. Don't worry about going back for seconds with all those veggies! This is my new go-to!
ingredients: 2 tablespoons coconut aminos teriyaki sauce, divided
½ large green bell pepper, thinly sliced
¼ large yellow onion, thinly sliced
1 large zucchini, cut into long strands
directions: Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon teriyaki sauce in a large skillet over medium heat
Add carrot, bell pepper, and onion; cook and stir until onions are translucent, about 5 minutes
Stir in bok choy, zucchini, and garlic powder
Cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender, about 7 minutes
